# Work Item Writing Standards

Applies when drafting or editing work items, backlog items, or content under `docs/templates/`.

## Titles

- Start with a verb or capability noun; be specific
- Feature: `[Capability] — short outcome` (e.g., `Early Warning Score Display`)
- Story: user-facing outcome, not implementation (`Display EWS on Patient Monitor`, not `Add EWS API endpoint`)

## Descriptions

**Feature:** What it is + value delivered + Technical Readiness assessment

**Story:** Full user story sentence + link to parent Feature + Platform Decision and Rationale

**Task:** Work description + Definition of Done block:

```
Definition of Done:
I know that I am done when...
- [demonstrable criterion 1]
- [demonstrable criterion 2]
```

## Acceptance criteria (Stories)

- Given / When / Then format preferred
- Testable, observable, no hidden scope
- Created collaboratively with agile team

## Story points

Fibonacci only: 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21, 34, 55. Flag items outside sizing guidelines in `docs/futurestate-process.md`.

## Tags

Apply standard tags from `reference/wiki/future-state/standard-work-item-tags.md` when gaps exist (NeedsAC, NeedsDoD, etc.).

Templates: `docs/templates/feature.md`, `story.md`, `pi-objective.md`, `dependency-record.md`
